\title{Forwarding}

\p{A [[ITFA]] mitigation: the producing instruction's result is routed from the output of the execute stage directly to the input of the next instruction's execute stage, bypassing the register-file write and read. The dependent consumer can execute one cycle later instead of waiting for writeback.}

\p{Conceptually, the pipeline grows wiring rather than stages. The result is "forwarded" from where it appears to where it's needed.}
